    "discriminators": [
     "A large aerial shell: a LAUNCH thump, a delay, then the airburst — and very often a crackle and report train from the stars afterwards. So it is a burst that is NOT a clean single event: expect several onsets and a long, echoing, genuinely WIDE outdoor tail, because these are recorded at distance in the open.",
     "Against EXPLOSIONS-REAL: acoustically an aerial shell IS an explosion. The leans are the multi-onset structure (launch, burst, crackle) and the long reverberant open-air tail. Weak; text carries it.",
     "Against FIREWORKS-RECREATIONAL: SCALE, and this one is reliable. A commercial mortar has serious sub-200 Hz energy and a multi-second tail; a firecracker has almost none and dies instantly. low_band_energy and length_seconds are the split."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "EXPLReal",
