    "discriminators": [
     "A string of firecrackers is a dense STOCHASTIC crackle train: many sharp, bright, tiny reports with irregular spacing. Roman candles and bottle rockets add a whistle and a small pop.",
     "Against GUNS-AUTOMATIC — the other dense onset train in this taxonomy, and the test that matters: firecrackers are STOCHASTIC (onset_periodicity around 0.2, because a fuse burns at a ragged rate) while a machine gun is PERIODIC (around 0.75, because it is a machine). The charges are also tiny, so low_band_energy sits far below any firearm's. Those two features together make the boundary real.",
     "Against FIREWORKS-COMMERCIAL: scale. Almost no sub-200 Hz energy and no multi-second tail. Against FIRE-CRACKLE: a fire crackle is far quieter with a much lower crest factor per event."
    ],
